03:16.312 --> 03:17.522
You have to go.

03:17.589 --> 03:18.742
I want to do it.

03:18.809 --> 03:20.596
Yeah, but you have to go.

03:23.157 --> 03:25.340
Wait.
Let me just wash my hands.

03:25.407 --> 03:26.771
You're gonna be late.

03:26.838 --> 03:28.834
- It's okay.
- I can do it.

03:28.901 --> 03:30.456
Helen, it'll take
two minutes.

03:30.523 --> 03:31.682
Yeah, I know, but I know

03:31.749 --> 03:33.054
how stressed-out you get
when you're late.

03:33.121 --> 03:34.866
Just... It's okay.

03:36.328 --> 03:37.663
- You sure?
- Yeah.

03:37.730 --> 03:39.451
I'll just do my upper thigh.

03:40.655 --> 03:42.343
- Okay.
- Okay.

03:43.490 --> 03:45.041
Hey, Vik.

03:46.320 --> 03:49.701
Uh, have your...
have your parents said anything?

03:50.970 --> 03:52.315
At all?

03:52.490 --> 03:54.068
About what?

03:57.151 --> 03:58.889
I'll see you later today
at Dr. Roper's?

03:58.956 --> 04:01.256
- Yep. I'll be there.
- Okay.

04:14.449 --> 04:17.173
Come on, hurry up.
I don't want to be late.

04:17.240 --> 04:19.450
Mom left me your lunch,
so I'll get that for you

04:19.517 --> 04:20.826
and then we got to go.

04:20.892 --> 04:22.128
Bye, guys!

04:22.196 --> 04:24.866
- Have good days!
- Bye, Vik!

04:25.394 --> 04:27.582
Hey, give me back my notebook.

04:58.097 --> 05:00.083
I'm telling you,
all the new immigrants

05:00.150 --> 05:03.858
from Lebanon, they have it
so much easier than we did.

05:03.925 --> 05:05.923
They go to the top right away.

05:05.990 --> 05:08.402
Like that Amal Clooney.

05:08.490 --> 05:11.494
She's not exactly
a new immigrant, Dad.

05:11.561 --> 05:13.304
Think she went to NYU.

05:14.673 --> 05:16.848
Does this really work?

05:17.329 --> 05:19.986
Yeah. It can read your
glucose values in real time.

05:20.053 --> 05:21.912
Why do you have to change it
every two weeks?

05:21.979 --> 05:23.273
That's so inconvenient.

05:23.340 --> 05:24.840
Or you could just go back

05:24.907 --> 05:26.554
to pricking your finger
once a day.

05:33.032 --> 05:35.411
Okay. You're good.

05:37.220 --> 05:38.729
I have this customer

05:38.796 --> 05:40.310
- who's a doctor.
- Mm-hmm.

05:40.377 --> 05:41.825
Have I told you
about him?

05:41.931 --> 05:43.869
You have, but he's not a doctor.

05:43.936 --> 05:45.499
He's a physician's assistant.

05:45.566 --> 05:47.864
Here, there is no difference.

05:48.443 --> 05:49.797
There is, in fact.

05:49.864 --> 05:51.720
He can write prescriptions.

05:51.787 --> 05:52.799
What about him?

05:52.866 --> 05:54.068
He says, in America,

05:54.135 --> 05:55.959
there's no art left
to medicine.

05:56.026 --> 05:59.396
It's basically just machines
doing the diagnosing.

05:59.463 --> 06:02.661
In a few years, there will be
no need for surgeons anymore.

06:02.948 --> 06:05.215
A robot will do your job.

06:05.574 --> 06:07.317
Things to think about.

06:10.032 --> 06:11.926
How's the Prius working out?

06:11.993 --> 06:13.794
It's a good car, right?

06:14.616 --> 06:15.735
Ah...

06:15.803 --> 06:17.033
You don't like it?

06:17.170 --> 06:19.158
Yeah, sure, I like
that it saves gas,

06:19.225 --> 06:21.355
but... sometimes
I want something

06:21.422 --> 06:23.752
with a little bit more zip,
you know. Power.

06:23.819 --> 06:25.248
Especially here
in L.A., you know.

06:25.315 --> 06:27.625
The bastards,
they cut me off all the time.

06:27.692 --> 06:28.722
What can I do?

06:28.789 --> 06:30.994
I got this little
putt-putt car.

06:31.061 --> 06:32.659
Yeah, what did you want, Dad?
A Porsche?

06:32.726 --> 06:34.809
Hey.
What's with the tone?

06:34.876 --> 06:36.231
You asked, I told you.

06:36.298 --> 06:38.307
- Why are you upset?
- I'm not upset.

06:38.374 --> 06:40.774
He's not upset.
You're the one who sounds upset.

06:40.841 --> 06:42.709
- I am not upset.
- Why can't you be

06:42.776 --> 06:45.099
more thankful to Vik
for taking care of us?

06:45.166 --> 06:46.758
Of course
I am thankful.

06:46.825 --> 06:47.994
He knows that.

06:48.061 --> 06:49.388
I'm just saying,
maybe we should

06:49.455 --> 06:51.497
have better
communication.

06:53.469 --> 06:54.648
Look.

06:57.164 --> 06:59.144
Speaking of communication,

06:59.404 --> 07:01.762
there are a few details
I want to go over.

07:02.448 --> 07:05.660
First, um,
about my life insurance.

07:06.436 --> 07:09.371
You should know,
it's about a million dollars,

07:09.438 --> 07:11.980
and you guys are
the beneficiaries.

07:18.157 --> 07:20.758
I've kept my overhead pretty low

07:20.825 --> 07:22.044
for most of my life.

07:22.111 --> 07:24.074
Until you met Helen.

07:25.705 --> 07:28.590
So I've got decent savings,

07:28.915 --> 07:30.558
all of which will go to you.

07:34.032 --> 07:36.637
Um, also...

07:37.180 --> 07:38.695
before I get too sick,

07:38.762 --> 07:40.363
I will make sure...

07:40.911 --> 07:42.133
What...

07:45.415 --> 07:47.489
Why do you have to be
so cruel, Vikram?

07:47.556 --> 07:49.224
- So heartless.
- What?

07:49.291 --> 07:51.386
We all heard
what Helen said.

07:51.453 --> 07:52.846
Do you think we're deaf?

07:52.949 --> 07:56.178
And now you have to go
and rub it in our faces?

08:10.948 --> 08:12.332
Listen, Ma.

08:12.890 --> 08:14.954
Helen and I are...

08:16.269 --> 08:18.316
We're working on having a baby.

08:20.156 --> 08:21.811
A grandchild.

08:22.878 --> 08:24.442
For you and Baba.

08:28.453 --> 08:30.804
Helen is too old to have a baby.

08:30.985 --> 08:32.254
No, actually,

08:32.321 --> 08:34.644
there are a lot
of new treatments now.

08:35.073 --> 08:37.566
Women are having children
well into their 50s.

08:38.282 --> 08:40.419
And we've been seeing
a fertility doctor

08:40.486 --> 08:41.458
for weeks.

08:46.568 --> 08:48.571
Hmm? Hmm?

09:09.974 --> 09:11.090
How is she?

09:11.157 --> 09:12.162
Is everything okay?

09:12.229 --> 09:13.821
The surgery went very smoothly.

09:13.888 --> 09:14.992
Now, Jenny's recovering.

09:15.059 --> 09:17.290
You should be able
to see her in about an hour.

09:18.324 --> 09:20.012
- Thank God.
- Thank you.

09:20.079 --> 09:22.407
Let's sit,
talk about next steps.

09:29.098 --> 09:31.840
Now, I did find tumors,

09:31.907 --> 09:33.492
which we are
sending away for tests.

09:33.559 --> 09:34.992
Wait. What does that mean?

09:35.059 --> 09:36.840
You-you said
everything went well.

09:36.907 --> 09:38.282
Well, until we get
the results back,

09:38.349 --> 09:39.770
there's no way of knowing
whether they're

09:39.837 --> 09:41.290
malignant or benign.

09:42.115 --> 09:43.825
M-Malignant
meaning what?

09:43.892 --> 09:45.557
Malignant
meaning cancer?

09:45.624 --> 09:47.493
We really don't know.

09:47.809 --> 09:50.102
But I'm going to be
honest with you.

09:50.407 --> 09:52.153
Jenny could have liver cancer.

09:52.220 --> 09:53.852
Now, I stress "could,"

09:53.919 --> 09:55.762
- because there's...
- No!

09:57.669 --> 10:00.772
Even if the tests
confirm malignancy,

10:00.839 --> 10:02.545
there are lots of good options.

10:02.612 --> 10:05.020
- No, no, no!
- Dr. Mattu in pediatric oncology

10:05.087 --> 10:07.126
is probably the best
in the country.

10:07.193 --> 10:07.803
- Honey.
- No!

10:07.870 --> 10:09.757
We'll set you up with a
consultation immediately,

10:09.824 --> 10:12.727
just in case,
so you understand the options.

10:13.376 --> 10:16.189
If this is worst-case scenario,

10:16.857 --> 10:17.908
these cancers...

10:17.975 --> 10:21.687
No! No!

10:21.755 --> 10:24.032
- No, no.
- Honey...

10:24.099 --> 10:26.626
- Please!
- These cancers...

10:27.396 --> 10:32.188
can be very specifically
targeted nowadays.

10:32.477 --> 10:34.428
It's not fair!

10:34.495 --> 10:36.045
She's just
a little girl!

10:36.112 --> 10:38.766
Honey, the doctor's saying
they don't know yet.

10:40.466 --> 10:44.657
Mr. Rodriguez,

10:44.724 --> 10:48.293
our social worker,
he is on the premises.

10:48.360 --> 10:50.771
No! No!

10:52.380 --> 10:56.073
No, no!

10:56.286 --> 10:57.940
No!

10:58.404 --> 10:59.575
Excuse me.

10:59.643 --> 11:01.915
No! Please!

11:18.657 --> 11:20.824
Have you been keeping up
on the injections?

11:21.032 --> 11:22.368
Yes, I have.

11:22.435 --> 11:24.415
Hopefully, this will
all be worth it.

11:26.032 --> 11:27.832
Let's take a look
at those follicles.

11:34.230 --> 11:35.438
Success?

11:37.719 --> 11:38.872
Why don't you get dressed,

11:38.939 --> 11:41.634
and we'll meet in my office
and discuss next steps.

12:09.797 --> 12:11.032
I'm sorry.

12:11.305 --> 12:14.418
Please, don't apologize.

12:14.733 --> 12:15.884
It's not your fault.

12:15.951 --> 12:17.324
Actually, it is.

12:17.961 --> 12:19.453
Stop.

12:19.907 --> 12:21.762
- Because of your age?
- No.

12:24.850 --> 12:26.855
I haven't been doing the shots.

12:29.265 --> 12:31.410
- What do you mean?
- What I just said.

12:32.063 --> 12:33.593
You haven't been
injecting yourself?

12:33.660 --> 12:35.840
No. Not all the time.

12:35.907 --> 12:37.296
Not as much as I'm
supposed to be.

12:37.363 --> 12:38.617
Helen.

12:39.531 --> 12:41.429
This is costing us 11 grand.

12:41.496 --> 12:42.449
I-I know.

12:42.517 --> 12:43.660
I don't understand.

12:43.727 --> 12:44.830
Well, I can't do it alone.

12:44.897 --> 12:45.927
You're not
doing it alone.

12:45.994 --> 12:46.986
I'm right here.

12:47.053 --> 12:48.130
I left work to be here.

12:48.197 --> 12:49.239
That's not
what I mean.

12:49.306 --> 12:52.808
Vik, a child is a lot of work.

12:52.990 --> 12:54.992
I want to give you
what you want...

12:55.059 --> 12:56.658
I really do...
But I can't

12:56.725 --> 12:59.606
go through that again
if you're not gonna be here.

12:59.750 --> 13:01.091
You fucking lied to me.

13:01.158 --> 13:02.809
I know. I'm sorry.

13:02.876 --> 13:05.168
I told my parents
we were having a baby.

13:05.235 --> 13:06.488
I don't know what to do
about your parents.

13:06.555 --> 13:07.915
- What is wrong with you?!
- If you want me

13:07.982 --> 13:09.810
to have your baby,
you have to at least try

13:09.877 --> 13:11.582
to be here with me
while I do it.

13:11.848 --> 13:13.502
Every single day, your odds

13:13.569 --> 13:16.078
of beating this thing
get less and less.

13:16.145 --> 13:17.617
We cannot waste any more time.

13:17.684 --> 13:19.324
We have to make some choices.

13:25.490 --> 13:26.578
I gotta get back to work.

13:26.645 --> 13:29.020
- No, you don't.
- Yes, I do.

13:37.866 --> 13:39.426
<i>How is she?
Is everything okay?</i>

13:39.493 --> 13:40.601
<i>Well, I can't do it alone.</i>

13:40.668 --> 13:42.578
Afternoon, Dr. Ullah.
Busy day?

13:42.645 --> 13:44.387
They all are.

13:45.778 --> 13:47.816
<i>Helen is too old
to have a baby.</i>

13:47.883 --> 13:49.115
<i>I haven't been
doing the shots.</i>

13:49.182 --> 13:51.082
<i>Why do you have
to be so cruel, Vikram?</i>

13:51.149 --> 13:52.457
<i>- Success?
- So heartless.</i>

13:52.524 --> 13:53.723
<i>We cannot waste any more time.</i>

13:53.790 --> 13:56.055
<i>You have to at least try to
be here with me while I do it.</i>

13:56.122 --> 13:57.870
- <i>Have your parents said anything?</i>
- Dr. Ullah.

13:57.937 --> 13:59.573
Everything okay?

13:59.657 --> 14:01.617
<i>She's just a little girl!</i>

14:01.684 --> 14:03.621
Yeah, uh...

14:05.657 --> 14:06.975
I'm such an idiot.

14:07.042 --> 14:09.231
I forgot, I have
a meeting downtown.

14:09.298 --> 14:10.375
Okay.

14:10.443 --> 14:11.922
Drive safely.

14:45.468 --> 14:47.488
How much is that Porsche?

14:49.110 --> 14:51.973
That's the 911
Turbo S Cabriolet.

14:52.344 --> 14:56.308
580 horsepower,
zero to 60 in 2.8 seconds,

14:56.375 --> 14:59.824
and a 3.8-liter engine
with very little turbo lag.

15:01.508 --> 15:02.973
So, how much?

15:03.766 --> 15:05.415
205 K.

15:09.196 --> 15:11.145
You take American Express?

15:13.136 --> 15:15.740
Do you want to take it
for a test drive, sir?

15:16.157 --> 15:17.446
Nah.

15:18.995 --> 15:20.430
Whew.

15:20.825 --> 15:22.332
I just like it.

16:07.443 --> 16:08.575
Vik?

16:11.012 --> 16:12.228
What are you doing?

16:12.295 --> 16:14.243
Hey, Sierra.

16:14.893 --> 16:18.088
