who made this board,

29:25.893 --> 29:27.772
and I think it came
from around here in Morro Bay.

29:27.839 --> 29:28.914
Oh.

29:29.656 --> 29:31.553
- You mind?
- Nope. Go ahead.

29:32.657 --> 29:33.782
Wow.

29:34.367 --> 29:35.595
It's beautiful.

29:35.774 --> 29:37.637
Thank you.
It's my father's.

29:38.242 --> 29:39.574
Hey, Joe.

29:39.805 --> 29:41.512
You come take a look at this?

29:44.425 --> 29:46.361
- Hey. I'm Cole.
- Joey.

29:46.428 --> 29:48.241
Nice to meet
you, Joey.

29:48.308 --> 29:49.887
Let me see this.

29:51.782 --> 29:54.793
Well, this is
original, huh?

29:55.755 --> 29:58.816
We see a, uh, lot
of wooden kit boards,

29:58.883 --> 30:00.325
but not many
like this.

30:00.392 --> 30:02.236
You, uh...
you selling?

30:02.303 --> 30:04.558
No, no. Just trying
to figure out who made it.

30:04.625 --> 30:05.853
From around here?

30:05.920 --> 30:07.590
Well, could be anybody.

30:07.657 --> 30:09.130
Definitely 1970s, though.

30:09.197 --> 30:11.984
You got the classic nose
