surfboard I ever carved.

32:46.198 --> 32:47.324
So...

32:47.394 --> 32:50.078
what brings you
to Morro Bay, Cole?

32:50.394 --> 32:51.998
I'm not sure exactly.

32:52.254 --> 32:53.324
From...?

32:53.407 --> 32:55.637
- Montauk.
- Montauk.

32:56.873 --> 32:58.123
Amazing.

33:00.465 --> 33:01.324
Hi there.

33:01.407 --> 33:02.961
Uh, I'll just be a sec.

33:05.235 --> 33:09.122
Um, how long are you in town?

33:11.286 --> 33:12.975
I don't know, really.

33:13.094 --> 33:15.106
I mean, I just got here, so...

33:15.303 --> 33:17.366
Why don't you come by tonight?

33:17.657 --> 33:20.470
I host a weekly salon.

33:20.798 --> 33:21.867
If you're anything

33:21.934 --> 33:23.115
like your father,

33:23.182 --> 33:25.051
I think
you'd like it.

33:27.821 --> 33:29.362
Sure.

33:44.927 --> 33:47.176
I'm so glad you found me, Cole.

33:50.910 --> 33:52.259
Thank you.

33:56.711 --> 33:58.149
I'm sorry.

33:58.727 --> 34:01.957
This piece over here is
the one you had your eye on?

34:09.525 --> 34:14.223
If these pellets are
just compressed protein,

34:14.290 --> 34:17.371
why deplete
the ocean for them?

34:17.907 --> 34:21.512
Now, as an entrepreneur, John...

34:21.657 --> 34:23.033
This is over my head.

34:23.100 --> 34:24.721
No, it is not.

34:24.917 --> 34:26.105
Sit up and listen.

34:27.947 --> 34:30.259
Oh, look. There he is.

34:30.326 --> 34:34.081
Everyone, here stands
a gift from the past.

34:34.251 --> 34:36.902
The son of a man
I used to know.

34:37.016 --> 34:38.554
You know, they say

34:38.625 --> 34:40.523
time moves in a straight line,

34:40.590 --> 34:42.887
but really,
it moves in circles.

34:43.007 --> 34:45.090
I'm so glad you made it.

34:47.114 --> 34:48.443
Thanks
for the invite.

34:48.510 --> 34:50.195
Yep. Oh, thank you.

34:50.262 --> 34:51.485
Very nice.

34:51.632 --> 34:53.534
Nice place
you got here.

34:53.601 --> 34:55.469
It absorbs people.

34:55.570 --> 34:57.426
That's what I love about it.

35:07.204 --> 35:09.762
That's my protégée, Delphine.

35:09.922 --> 35:11.660
Isn't she beautiful?

35:14.145 --> 35:15.863
I'm married.

35:16.748 --> 35:18.328
So, being married prevents you

35:18.395 --> 35:21.718
from forming an opinion
about a beautiful woman?

35:22.524 --> 35:24.655
No, not at all.

35:26.476 --> 35:27.810
Here.

35:27.878 --> 35:29.002
Whoa. Hey, what are you doing?

35:29.069 --> 35:30.543
It's okay.

35:30.886 --> 35:32.971
Poor guy.
You're all bound up.

35:35.310 --> 35:36.891
Take a breath.

35:36.958 --> 35:38.512
A deep one.

35:39.838 --> 35:42.444
Go ahead. It's not
gonna kill you.

35:46.919 --> 35:49.290
And let it out slowly.

35:56.033 --> 35:57.317
Better?

36:02.614 --> 36:05.079
What was your relationship
to my father?

36:06.576 --> 36:08.211
We were lovers.

36:11.278 --> 36:13.086
For how long?

36:13.657 --> 36:15.610
Oh, a few months.

36:15.741 --> 36:17.215
It was the late '70s.

36:17.282 --> 36:18.908
Everyone loved someone.

36:18.975 --> 36:21.220
That summer,
I loved your father.

36:22.699 --> 36:24.449
And then?

36:24.517 --> 36:25.809
Nothing.

36:25.907 --> 36:27.840
He went home.

36:27.907 --> 36:30.700
I met someone else.
Life moved on.

36:30.767 --> 36:32.344
What about
the surfboard?

36:33.317 --> 36:35.516
You know what
Freud said.

36:35.811 --> 36:39.032
Sometimes a cigar
is just a cigar.

36:39.800 --> 36:41.044
Delphine.

36:41.574 --> 36:43.079
This is Cole.

36:43.185 --> 36:45.454
Cole, this is
Delphine.

36:45.872 --> 36:47.122
Hi, Cole.

36:47.190 --> 36:48.567
Hi.

36:50.120 --> 36:51.685
Want some?

36:54.254 --> 36:55.552
Sure.

37:00.935 --> 37:02.677
Oh, shit.

37:17.613 --> 37:19.196
So...

37:19.490 --> 37:21.240
So?

37:22.563 --> 37:24.752
You want to
tell me about it?

37:26.071 --> 37:27.665
Tell you about what?

37:27.732 --> 37:30.218
No one drives all the way
across the country

37:30.285 --> 37:32.572
just to see about a surfboard.
Okay.

37:35.749 --> 37:37.914
What's going on
in your marriage?

37:38.832 --> 37:41.602
Luisa and I are working
through some things.

37:41.669 --> 37:43.399
Your father was also

37:43.466 --> 37:45.035
going through a hard time
in his marriage

37:45.102 --> 37:46.710
when he got here.

37:47.285 --> 37:48.936
How long was he here for?

37:49.032 --> 37:50.410
Not long.

37:51.456 --> 37:53.390
Four or five months.

37:53.785 --> 37:55.960
And the two of you
were together?

37:56.143 --> 37:58.007
For a while, yes.

38:02.058 --> 38:05.971
I never really thought
he got out of Montauk much.

38:06.038 --> 38:08.739
Oh, no, he traveled quite a bit.

38:08.806 --> 38:09.862
I think.

38:10.089 --> 38:11.921
Or he wanted to.

38:12.648 --> 38:15.468
I can't remember.
I just remember a...

38:15.791 --> 38:19.647
great, big, adventurous soul.

38:21.074 --> 38:23.663
I wouldn't describe him
as adventurous.

38:23.894 --> 38:25.240
Okay.

38:25.464 --> 38:27.280
How would you describe him?

38:28.772 --> 38:30.121
Drunk.

38:31.506 --> 38:33.081
Abusive.

38:34.333 --> 38:36.054
Emotionally absent.

38:36.963 --> 38:39.311
Chronically depressed.

38:39.699 --> 38:41.183
Wow.

38:41.964 --> 38:44.983
Doesn't sound like
the Gabriel I knew at all.

38:51.160 --> 38:52.757
How is your mother?

38:52.907 --> 38:55.288
Cherry is fine.

38:55.529 --> 38:57.561
Cherry's good, actually.

38:59.675 --> 39:01.397
Are they still together?

39:02.253 --> 39:04.304
No, he's dead, Nan.

39:07.277 --> 39:08.449
What?

39:08.867 --> 39:10.367
He's dead.

39:12.198 --> 39:14.960
I'm sorry. I figured
you would've known that.

39:16.097 --> 39:17.407
When?

39:17.893 --> 39:19.331
Years ago.

39:19.464 --> 39:21.194
I was a little boy.

39:23.471 --> 39:25.077
Oh, my God.

39:26.714 --> 39:28.858
Wow, Gabriel.

39:39.688 --> 39:41.206
I...

39:41.861 --> 39:44.425
I need some air, love. Um...

39:44.741 --> 39:46.811
when you're ready to go to bed,

39:46.878 --> 39:49.303
Delphine will show you
to your room.

39:56.503 --> 39:58.194
You an artist, too?

39:59.029 --> 40:00.753
I paint.

40:01.932 --> 40:03.373
Where you from?

40:04.401 --> 40:05.690
Idaho.

40:06.105 --> 40:07.917
Idaho?

40:08.472 --> 40:10.581
Oh, man.

40:12.424 --> 40:14.256
How long you been out here?

40:14.564 --> 40:17.183
I met Nan
at a trade show

40:17.250 --> 40:19.507
maybe...
five years ago?

40:19.574 --> 40:22.100
And followed her
to California to study.

40:22.324 --> 40:26.248
She lets me stay for free
as long as I help out a bit.

40:30.323 --> 40:32.733
It gets bright in here
in the mornings.

40:33.589 --> 40:35.686
Let the shower run for a minute.

40:35.753 --> 40:37.887
It takes a little while
for it to get hot.

40:39.216 --> 40:41.733
Okay. Thank you.

41:02.691 --> 41:04.381
What are you doing?

41:08.748 --> 41:10.895
I come with the room.

41:17.339 --> 41:19.110
What kind of game
are you playing here?

41:19.177 --> 41:20.721
I'm married.

41:20.854 --> 41:22.174
Okay.

41:22.407 --> 41:24.186
Look, I don't know who you are,

41:24.253 --> 41:25.273
and I don't know
what this place is,

41:25.340 --> 41:27.734
but I came here to find out why
my father came to California,

41:27.801 --> 41:30.244
- not to cheat on my wife.
- Okay, then don't.

41:30.311 --> 41:32.627
Well, I'm trying not to,
but it's a little difficult

41:32.694 --> 41:34.742
when you got a half-naked
woman in your bed.

41:34.809 --> 41:36.549
Ask her to leave.

41:37.990 --> 41:40.701
I'm sure she was
just trying to help.

41:40.768 --> 41:43.992
You seem wound so tight, Cole.

41:44.059 --> 41:45.284
To help?

41:46.206 --> 41:48.319
I don't need that kind of help.

41:48.741 --> 41:51.554
I can't believe I have
to even explain this to you.

41:51.924 --> 41:53.529
Maybe I shouldn't
be surprised, though.

41:53.596 --> 41:55.156
I mean, you slept with
my father when he was married,

41:55.223 --> 41:57.312
so clearly marriage isn't
that much of a problem to you.

41:57.379 --> 42:00.717
Actually, your father's marriage
was my biggest problem.

42:02.198 --> 42:03.897
What is that supposed to mean?

42:09.791 --> 42:11.611
What is this? A love letter?

42:11.678 --> 42:12.690
Yes.

42:12.758 --> 42:14.459
I have a whole box
of them.

42:21.573 --> 42:23.389
When did he write all those?

42:23.964 --> 42:25.640
We wrote to each other
on and off

42:25.707 --> 42:27.492
after he left Morro Bay.

42:27.559 --> 42:28.897
For how long?

42:29.115 --> 42:30.982
About ten years.

42:31.049 --> 42:33.595
I thought you said
it was a brief affair.

42:35.029 --> 42:36.529
I lied.

42:42.770 --> 42:44.936
I can't believe he's dead.

42:47.582 --> 42:51.334
There was a time I thought
he was my be'shert.

42:52.541 --> 42:54.444
Do you know
what that word means?

42:55.315 --> 42:57.639
It means soul mate.

42:57.706 --> 42:59.209
My destiny.

42:59.549 --> 43:00.940
Look.

43:04.972 --> 43:06.180
You see?

43:09.563 --> 43:11.096
"N"...

43:12.693 --> 43:14.025
"G."

43:19.339 --> 43:22.029
That surfboard
was his favorite thing.

43:23.003 --> 43:25.147
We met down at the beach.

43:26.657 --> 43:30.053
I'd seen him
around town before, but...

43:30.256 --> 43:32.811
he was such a loner.

43:32.878 --> 43:34.680
He always kept to himself.

43:37.397 --> 43:41.100
I asked him if I could
take pictures of him.

43:42.287 --> 43:43.792
He was...

43:44.393 --> 43:46.670
so handsome, so...

43:46.745 --> 43:48.370
striking.

43:48.924 --> 43:51.795
After that first night,
we were never apart

43:52.015 --> 43:53.662
for four months.

43:55.907 --> 43:58.623
He called me "Wild Eyes."

44:03.284 --> 44:06.846
He said he didn't know women
like me existed in the world.

44:09.336 --> 44:10.982
I'll show you.

44:12.990 --> 44:14.681
"You asked me what I want

44:14.748 --> 44:16.137
from you, my love.

44:16.221 --> 44:18.178
My answer is simple.

44:18.471 --> 44:19.890
First, your mind.

44:19.957 --> 44:21.686
Then your body.

44:22.115 --> 44:23.819
Then your soul."

44:32.160 --> 44:34.014
So, why'd he leave?

44:36.619 --> 44:38.670
Cherry was pregnant.

44:39.506 --> 44:41.997
She wrote that if
he didn't come home,

44:42.064 --> 44:44.601
she would kill herself.

44:46.532 --> 44:47.760
What?

44:48.440 --> 44:50.061
So he left.

44:59.057 --> 45:01.334
And then what?
He just stopped writing?

45:01.901 --> 45:04.406
No, but his letters

45:04.473 --> 45:07.787
became more sad, bitter.

45:08.104 --> 45:10.773
They kept having more kids,
he felt trapped,

45:10.840 --> 45:14.506
and the thought of me
was just making him miserable.

45:14.702 --> 45:18.186
So I devised a plan,

45:18.626 --> 45:22.756
a way to extract me
from his heart and his head.

45:23.479 --> 45:25.740
To forget me once and for all.

45:26.214 --> 45:29.154
An exorcism of sorts.

45:31.157 --> 45:32.623
Did it work?

45:33.268 --> 45:34.586
It did.

45:34.654 --> 45:36.342
How do you know that?

45:36.532 --> 45:38.472
Because the last task,

45:38.539 --> 45:41.935
the final instruction,
if he finally knew

45:42.002 --> 45:44.725
he was no longer
in love with me,

45:45.196 --> 45:47.990
was to send my letters back.

45:48.893 --> 45:50.554
All of them.

45:54.883 --> 45:56.488
And here they are.

46:00.365 --> 46:02.233
I'm sorry, Nan.

46:03.182 --> 46:05.053
Don't be, sweetheart.

46:05.211 --> 46:07.381
We wanted different things.

46:07.574 --> 46:09.975
I have no regrets.

46:13.240 --> 46:14.920
Don't worry.

46:16.448 --> 46:18.248
Neither did he.

46:29.670 --> 46:32.283
<i>You've reached the
voice mail of Alison and...</i>

46:32.350 --> 46:33.382
<i>Joanie!</i>

46:33.449 --> 46:35.748
We can't get
to the phone right now so...

46:38.471 --> 46:40.026
Fuck.

47:23.988 --> 47:26.108
How did the exorcism work?

47:27.344 --> 47:30.311
I sent your father
five final letters,

47:30.690 --> 47:32.343
one at a time.

47:32.472 --> 47:35.225
Each one with a task.

47:35.699 --> 47:37.750
Every time he completed a task,

47:37.817 --> 47:39.521
I sent him another.

47:43.550 --> 47:45.152
Read this.

47:54.657 --> 47:57.095
"Find my scent in nature."

47:57.198 --> 47:59.012
Delphine will help you.

48:02.790 --> 48:08.077
<i>♪ I am not the only traveler ♪</i>

48:10.357 --> 48:14.616
<i>♪ Who has not
repaid his debt ♪</i>

48:16.517 --> 48:20.369
<i>♪ I've been searching
for a trail ♪</i>

48:20.436 --> 48:23.350
<i>♪ To follow again ♪</i>

48:23.511 --> 48:25.492
<i>♪ Take me back ♪</i>

48:25.559 --> 48:29.179
<i>♪ To the night we met ♪</i>

48:30.841 --> 48:33.530
<i>♪ And then I can ♪</i>

48:33.674 --> 48:36.374
<i>♪ Tell myself ♪</i>

48:38.240 --> 48:43.671
<i>♪ What the hell
I'm supposed to do ♪</i>

48:45.313 --> 48:50.641
<i>♪ And then I can tell myself ♪</i>

48:52.324 --> 48:54.921
<i>♪ Not to ride along... ♪</i>

48:54.988 --> 48:56.210
"Task two.

48:56.682 --> 49:00.534
Write down everything
you love about me,

49:00.741 --> 49:03.354
and then wrap the words
around my scent."

49:04.265 --> 49:06.963
I love that she always
calls me on my shit.

49:10.186 --> 49:11.963
I love how smart she is.

49:13.007 --> 49:15.823
I love how she deals
with grief head-on.

49:16.663 --> 49:18.429
When our boy died...

49:21.791 --> 49:26.063
I couldn't admit
my own grief, so...

49:26.324 --> 49:29.450
I made her carry the burden
for the both of us.

49:32.696 --> 49:35.372
I made her feel
like she was the weak one.

49:40.336 --> 49:42.037
I made her feel
like she was going crazy

49:42.104 --> 49:43.568
so I wouldn't lose my own mind.

49:43.635 --> 49:46.162
<i>♪ I had all
and then most of you ♪</i>

49:46.229 --> 49:49.586
<i>♪ Some and now none of you ♪</i>

49:50.387 --> 49:52.203
<i>♪ Take me back ♪</i>

49:52.270 --> 49:53.701
<i>♪ To the night we met... ♪</i>

49:53.768 --> 49:56.137
"Number three.
Build a pyre.

49:56.434 --> 49:59.470
Imbue each stone with
something you hate about me.

49:59.549 --> 50:01.878
Add the smell
and the things you love.

50:03.365 --> 50:05.542
And then set it all ablaze."

50:11.616 --> 50:13.869
I hate how unforgiving you are.

50:16.985 --> 50:20.632
I hate that you never told me
how unhappy you were.

50:20.780 --> 50:25.689
I hate that you ran off
with Noah fucking Solloway.

50:26.628 --> 50:29.133
And I hate what shitty taste
you have in men.

50:29.200 --> 50:31.760
That you are always picking guys
who don't deserve you.

50:32.592 --> 50:34.924
I hate that you gave up on me.

50:41.694 --> 50:44.923
I hate that I can't
give up on you.

50:48.157 --> 50:49.605
What do you want?

50:49.758 --> 50:52.762
Before you do this, you need
to state your intention.

50:57.490 --> 51:01.472
I want to be free of you.

51:02.938 --> 51:05.888
<i>♪ I had all
and then most of you ♪</i>

51:05.955 --> 51:08.949
<i>♪ Some and now none of you ♪</i>

51:10.403 --> 51:14.717
<i>♪ Take me back
to the night we met ♪</i>

51:17.351 --> 51:20.169
<i>♪ I don't know
what I'm supposed to do ♪</i>

51:20.236 --> 51:23.159
<i>♪ Haunted by the ghost of you ♪</i>

51:24.226 --> 51:29.776
<i>♪ Oh, take me back
to the night we met ♪</i>

51:32.449 --> 51:34.262
<i>♪ When the night ♪</i>

51:34.372 --> 51:38.769
<i>♪ Was full of terrors ♪</i>

51:39.215 --> 51:40.970
<i>♪ And your eyes ♪</i>

51:41.037 --> 51:45.438
<i>♪ Were filled with tears ♪</i>

51:47.282 --> 51:51.429
<i>♪ When you had not
touched me yet ♪</i>

51:53.183 --> 51:55.205
<i>♪ Oh, take me back ♪</i>

51:55.402 --> 51:59.257
<i>♪ To the night we met ♪</i>

52:01.778 --> 52:03.658
<i>♪ I had all
and then most of you ♪</i>

52:03.725 --> 52:06.266
<i>♪ Some and now none of you ♪</i>

52:17.763 --> 52:19.535
Didn't work.

52:20.672 --> 52:22.311
I feel worse.

52:24.616 --> 52:26.324
I'm sorry.

52:27.461 --> 52:29.749
It worked on your dad.

52:32.948 --> 52:34.616
I have to go home.

52:35.636 --> 52:37.468
Back to your wife?

52:42.797 --> 52:45.235
Do you want to see
the final letter?

52:46.433 --> 52:47.644
Sure.

53:00.997 --> 53:02.858
"Now you've finished
all four tasks,

53:02.925 --> 53:05.241
and so the exorcism is complete.

53:06.160 --> 53:07.819
If it worked...

53:10.032 --> 53:12.077
and you no longer love me,

53:12.995 --> 53:15.178
send me these letters back
so I know.

53:15.542 --> 53:16.713
I remain yours...

53:16.780 --> 53:18.358
Mind, body and soul.

53:18.845 --> 53:20.136
Nan."

53:48.258 --> 53:51.035
Nan, my dad didn't send
these letters to you.

53:54.360 --> 53:56.082
What do you mean?

53:57.560 --> 54:00.402
It's postmarked
two years after he died.

54:06.579 --> 54:08.434
I don't understand.

54:12.670 --> 54:15.107
I think my mom
found those letters.

54:16.352 --> 54:18.582
And then read them,
and then sent them to you,

54:19.102 --> 54:22.074
hoping you'd think
they'd come from him.

54:32.545 --> 54:34.524
All this time, I...

54:35.923 --> 54:38.488
I thought he didn't
love me anymore.

54:48.365 --> 54:50.191
How did he die?

54:58.585 --> 55:01.230
He hung himself
on my tenth birthday.

55:07.091 --> 55:09.465
Couple weeks after
you sent that last one.

55:13.657 --> 55:16.656
<i>♪ "About Today" by The National ... ♪
plays</i>

55:16.723 --> 55:18.071
Cole.

55:21.907 --> 55:23.801
She wants you
to take this with you.

55:24.522 --> 55:26.251
Where are you going?

55:26.379 --> 55:27.918
I'm going home.

55:28.024 --> 55:29.551
Back to your wife?

55:30.314 --> 55:31.485
No.

55:37.188 --> 55:39.551
I tried to make it work
with my wife.

55:40.587 --> 55:43.855
She is a wonderful woman,
and she deserves more

55:43.922 --> 55:45.843
than somebody
who's just half there,

55:45.910 --> 55:48.535
and the truth is I'm in love
with somebody else.

55:50.366 --> 55:53.691
And I have tried for years
to get her out of my mind,

55:53.758 --> 55:56.082
but it just never works,
and I don't want

55:56.149 --> 55:57.968
to wake up in ten years
and want to kill myself

55:58.035 --> 56:00.441
'cause I was just trying
to do the right thing.

56:00.948 --> 56:02.629
So I'm going home.

56:03.540 --> 56:05.472
I'm gonna tell her how I feel.

56:05.616 --> 56:08.027
<i>♪ What could I say? ♪</i>

56:08.449 --> 56:09.946
What?

56:11.953 --> 56:14.178
She's lucky, whoever she is.

56:14.563 --> 56:16.910
<i>♪ I was far away... ♪</i>

56:16.992 --> 56:18.344
Delphine.

56:22.172 --> 56:23.902
I'm sorry about last night.

56:24.460 --> 56:26.941
Don't be. I wanted that.

56:28.412 --> 56:30.340
What are you doing here?

56:31.440 --> 56:34.636
Seriously, you're beautiful,
you're smart, you're talented.

56:34.703 --> 56:36.504
You could do whatever
you want to do,

56:36.571 --> 56:38.031
be with whoever
you want to be with.

56:38.098 --> 56:40.637
You don't have to be Nan's proxy
for the rest of your life.

56:40.735 --> 56:42.621
I like being her proxy.

56:42.722 --> 56:45.137
I think Nan's a genius.

56:45.956 --> 56:48.423
<i>♪ Are you awake? ♪</i>

56:48.490 --> 56:50.492
<i>♪ Yeah, I'm right here... ♪</i>

56:50.559 --> 56:53.308
Take care of your mind,
body and soul.

56:55.391 --> 56:56.922
You, too.

57:01.106 --> 57:03.835
<i>♪ About today ♪</i>

57:09.814 --> 57:12.785
<i>♪ How close am I ♪</i>

57:17.758 --> 57:20.613
<i>♪ To losing you? ♪</i>

57:28.078 --> 57:31.035
<i>♪ How close am I ♪</i>

57:34.245 --> 57:35.642
<i>Thanks, Dad.</i>

